    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to rulers of a country or province who act as the representative of their sovereign or king and who are empowered to act in the sovereign's name. They often rule on frontiers or in provinces distant from the seat of power of the state.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000042591/Webster's 9th New Collegiate Dictionary (1985)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere a gobernantes de un país o provincia quien actúa como representante de su soberano o rey y quien posee el poder para actuar en nombre del soberano. Frecuentemente gobiernan en provincias fronterizas distantes del poder del estado.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar heersers van een land of provincie die optreden als vertegenwoordiger van hun soeverein of koning, en die zijn gemachtigd te handelen uit naam van de soeverein. Zij heersen vaak over grensgebieden of in provincies die ver van de machtszetel van de staat zijn verwijderd.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指一個國家或行省之統治者，為最高在位者或國王的代理人，有資格以君主之名行使其權力。他們通常統治邊疆地區或是遠離國家權力中心的邊疆省份。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
